# 🌍 AWS Regions

AWS has multiple Regions across the world.

A Region is a geographical area where AWS maintains multiple data centers.

Examples:

- US East (N. Virginia)
- US East (Ohio)
- Europe (Frankfurt)
- Asia Pacific (Mumbai)
- Asia Pacific (Singapore)

Choose the region closest to your users to reduce latency.

---

# 🏢 Availability Zones (AZ)

Each AWS Region contains multiple Availability Zones.

Availability Zones are physically separate data centers connected with high-speed networking.

Benefits:

- High Availability
- Fault Tolerance
- Disaster Recovery
- Better Reliability

Example:

```
US East (Ohio)

├── us-east-2a
├── us-east-2b
└── us-east-2c
```

Deploying resources across multiple Availability Zones improves application availability.

