# 🎯 Summary

Amazon EC2 is a core AWS service that provides scalable virtual servers in the cloud. It removes the need to purchase and maintain physical hardware while allowing applications to be deployed quickly and efficiently.

By selecting the appropriate EC2 instance type, deploying resources in the right AWS Region and Availability Zone, and following security best practices, organizations can build reliable, scalable, and cost-effective cloud applications.

